05845nam a22009495i 9783110682021DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20202021gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106820217 a10.1515/97831106820212doi  a(DE-B1597)537724  a(OCoLC)1202450652  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aREL0170002bisacsh04aThe Concept of Peace in Judaism, Christianity and Islam /ced. by Georges Tamer. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2020] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (VI, 176 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aKey Concepts in Interreligious Discourses ;v800tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- tThe Concept of Peace in Judaism -- tThe Concept of Peace in Christianity -- tThe Concept of Peace in Islam -- tEpilogue -- tList of Contributors and Editors -- tIndex of Persons -- tIndex of Subjects0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe eighth volume of the series "Key Concepts of Interreligious Discourses" investigates the roots of the concept of "peace" in Judaism, Christianity and Islam and its relevance for the present time. Facing present violent conflicts waged and justified by religious ideas or reasons, peace building prevails in current debates about religion and peace. Here the central question is: How may traditional sources in religions help to put down the weapons and create a society in which everyone can live safely without hostilities and the threat of violence? When we take the Sacred Scriptures of Judaism, Christianity and Islam into consideration it becomes obvious that the term "peace" and its equivalents in Hebrew, Greek and Arabic describe, at first, an ideal state based on the "love" / "mercy" of God to his creation. It is a divine gift that brings inward peace to the individuum and outer peace resting upon justice and equality. One main task of Jews, Christian and Muslims in the history is to find out how to bring down this transcendent ideal upon earth. The volume presents the concept of "peace" in its different aspects as anchored in the traditions of Judaism, Christianity and Islam. It unfolds commonalities and differences between the three monotheistic religions as well as the manifold discourses about peace within these three traditions. The book offers fundamental knowledge about the specific understanding of peace in each one of these traditions, their interdependencies and their relationship to secular world views.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aDialog. 4aDiskurs. 4aFriedensbewegung. 4aInterreligiösitat. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh  aDialogue.  aInterreligious Discourse.  aPeace.1 aAfsaruddin, Asma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsaacs, Alick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStümke, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTamer, Georges, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTamer, Georges, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aThörner, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477